.TH "hex_to_bin" 9 "hex_to_bin" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hex_to_bin \- convert a hex digit to its real value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hex_to_bin
.BI "(char ch "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ch" 12
ascii character represents hex digit
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBhex_to_bin\fP converts one hex digit to its actual value or -1 in case of bad
input.
